meanings: A Korean word that means 'Part-time job' in English. Originally from the German vocabularies 'arbeit' which means 'work' in English.
1. Literally translated as 'Part time job runaway slave' (알바추노) 2. Refers to 'Those who quit their part time jobs without prior notice'.
